## Current Setup

### Frontend (index.html)
- Single-page app (SPA) — all logic in one file, ~1570 lines
- 0–5 scoring scale (6 levels)
- Organized by: physical boxes → rubrics (Single/Primary/Secondary) → skills
- Uses Chart.js for data visualization

### Backend (Google Apps Script)
- 6 function handlers: `getStudents`, `getBoxes`, `getRubrics`, `getSessions`, `submitSession`
- Google Sheet database with tabs:
  - **Students** (id | name | active | group)
  - **Boxes** (id | name | active)
  - **Rubrics** (id | callNumber | boxName | type | skillFocus | published | active)
  - **Skills** (id | rubricId | skillText | order)
  - **Sessions** (id | studentId | rubricId | evaluatorName | submittedAt | notes)
  - **Scores** (sessionId | skillId | score)

### Data
- **15 test students** (fake, for testing) with classroom groups
- **30 physical boxes**
- **46 rubrics** with 600+ skills (all real from rubric-library.json)
- **13 sample sessions** (from testing)

